headlines.description: Second-placed Inter Milan were held to a third successive 1-1 draw after Radja Nainggolan, on loan at Cagliari, equalised for the visitors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young sets up Inter goal in draw on debut

headlines.description: Lazio's 11-match winning run in Serie A was ended on Sunday following a 1-1 derby draw with AS Roma that was decided by two goalkeeping errors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pair of GK howlers see Roma and Lazio draw

headlines.description: Serie A leaders Juventus suffered a shock 2-1 defeat at Napoli on Sunday, with coach Maurizio Sarri returning to his former club for the first time,
headlines.shortLinkText: Ronaldo scores, but Napoli stun leaders Juve
